{
  "stem": "9168.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one afternoon, as I and another court reporter, Edna Malloy from Omaha, were preparing to go down to dinner, about 5 o'clock in the Grand Hotel, we heard and felt an enormous vibration, an explosion.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I knew the hotel had been bombed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We had had bomb drills before.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Hotels had been bombed in Stuttgart by the Nazi fanatics, who are still hiding, where Allied and US people lived.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so we rushed down three flights of stairs, meeting everyone else in the hotel rushing out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The Nazi fanatics had come out from under the walled city, the catacombs-- I don't know how many-- and thrown a bomb-- crossed the street and thrown a bomb into the big, glass-- pardon me-- windows of the Grand Hotel into the dining room.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it hit against a wall, over which two people had just departed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But the dining room was crowded.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And no one was killed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But there were injuries from flying glass and debris.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after that, the security around the Grand Hotel, which was a, you know, top security pass to get in beyond our American MPs at the front desk, one entrance, was tightly secured, too.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, we were never allowed to go out for this very reason.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because they would come out of the catacombs and shoot anybody on the street who looked like someone on the Allied payroll, yes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was the hazard that we knew we had to live with.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was part of our original orientation, if you will, to know that we were restricted.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You mentioned previously that you married an American MP.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
